  "rationale": "Both edits add priority for user-specified formatting over the default spec: EDIT_A says \"fully follows the user's explicit formatting override, or (if no override is specified) ... Markdown with LaTeX\", while EDIT_B says \"either the default Markdown with LaTeX extensions, OR a valid user/operator-specified alternative format\" and elaborates how to follow the override. Both broaden the original rule to cover user/operator overrides rather than only the default Markdown+LaTeX spec."
